records.addlTxt:
(Cases 21CF1043, 22CF896, 21CT7 are called at 2:10 PM) Defendant Joshua E. Westphal in court.  Attorney Kerry A. Kelm in court for Joshua E. Westphal.  Attorney Matthew Z Kirkpatrick in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant waives right to a preliminary hearing and Court accepts waiver in 21CF1043, 22CF896. 
Arraignment in 21CF1043, 22CF896 & Hearing in 21CT7 to be scheduled with Branch 1 Judicial Assistant.

Conditions:
No contact with S.S. or S.S.'s residence, co-defendant K.P.
No contact with anyone involved in illegal drug activities, except in a therapeutic setting.
Defendant to maintain absolute sobriety. 
Comply with Pre-Trial Monitoring Services with possible testing based on monitoring level. 
(Covers 22CF896, 21CT7, 21CF1043)

(11:08 AM cases 21CT7, 21CF1043, 22CF896 called.) Prosecuting attorney Tiffany M. Winter in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Joshua E. Westphal appeared by video, in custody in the Eau Claire County Jail. Attorney Sonia L Anderson appeared by video for Joshua E. Westphal. 
Attorney Anderson advises does not have a copy of the complaint for 22CF896 and advises will re-call the case once the complaint has been received.
(11:12 AM cases 21CT7, 21CF1043, 22CF896 re-called.) Prosecuting attorney Tiffany M. Winter in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Joshua E. Westphal appeared by video, in custody in the Eau Claire County Jail. Attorney Sonia L Anderson appeared by video for Joshua E. Westphal.
Court orders warrants are quashed.
Defendant waives formal reading of the complaint in 22CF896.
State requests $2,500.00 cash bond and cites reasoning. Attorney Anderson requests signature bond then requests cash bond of no more than $250.00 and cites reasoning.
Court orders $500.00 cash bond with conditions to cover all cases and previous conditions remain in effect.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 16, 2022 at 02:00 pm.

Conditions:
